1 (5) RAPE;
2 (6) SEXUAL OFFENSE IN THE FIRST DEGREE OR SECOND DEGREE;
3 (7) CHILD ABUSE IN THE FIRST DEGREE UNDER § 3–601 OF THE
4 CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE;
5 (8) SEXUAL ABUSE OF A MINOR UNDER § 3–602 OF THE CRIMINAL
6 LAW ARTICLE;
7 (9) A FELONY OFFENSE UNDER TITLE 3, SUBTITLE 11 OF THE
8 CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE;
9 (10) CONTINUING COURSE OF CONDUCT WITH A CHILD UNDER § 3–315
10 OF THE CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE;
11 (11) ASSAULT IN THE FIRST DEGREE;
12 (12) ASSAULT WITH INTENT TO MURDER;
13 (13) ASSAULT WITH INTENT TO RAPE; OR
14 (14) ASSAULT WITH INTENT TO COMMIT A SEXUAL OFFENSE IN THE
15 FIRST DEGREE OR SECOND DEGREE.
16 (B) THE DEPARTMENT MAY HIRE OR RETAIN AN INDIVIDUAL CONVICTED OF
17 A CRIME LISTED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION IF THE JUDGMENT OF
18 CONVICTION FOR THE CRIME WAS REVERSED OR VACATED.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
20 October 1, 2025.

